programmes.show_description: In Plain Sight: Discover over a hundred massive concrete arrows scattered across America, a mysterious hole in the middle of a lake in Southern California and more. (S1, ep 3)
In 1980, an Australian rancher witnesses a hovering UFO that shoots out a black tube-like object. A French biologist is left stunned when he spots a saucer-shaped craft in 1982. (S1, ep 11)
Teens on a Christian retreat spot an object land on a hill, emitting solid beams of light in 1972. In 1989, two Belgian police officers chase a triangular craft across fields. (S1, ep 12)
Decoding the Dragon Gods: A look at the fire-breathing dragons, appearing in tales throughout the ancient world and worshipped as the bringers of great knowledge. (S14, ep 9)
Bad criminals, death-defying rescues and chaos in the skies all feature as the mayhem continues in Chaos Uncut. (S1, ep 6)

Ripple Effect: This episode explores a catastrophic high-speed train crash in Spain, an out of control cruise liner in Venice, the Deepwater Horizon tragedy and more. (2 of 6)
The Shocker: An electric chair gives Rich the chance to curry favour with Les. Seth hatches a scheme that could make a fortune for the store. But will it work in practice? (S7, ep 2)
Worksop 2: David Dickinson travels the country, team in tow, hoping to snap up some good deals. But will the locals take the cash for their antiques or gamble at auction? (S10, ep 33)
Huddersfield 2: Join David Dickinson as more collectors try to sell their items to dealers. Will they strike a deal, or will they take a chance at auction instead? (S10, ep 68)
The Pickers encounter an obsessive collector of Coca-Cola memorabilia. Plus, examples of elegant American art glass command a high price. (S3, ep 4)
...Henry and Sam's Wreck-trospective. Henry and Sam visit the Classic Motor Show in Birmingham. (S1, ep 10)
Locker Mountain High: The auction action moves to Upland, where buyers Dan and Laura take their rivals on a wild ride. Desperate for treasure, Mary decides to spend early. (S7, ep 23)
Fontan-O-Rama: Dave surprises his rivals by showing his lighter side at auctions in Fontana. After scoring here in the past, Jarrod and Brandi arrive with high hopes. (S7, ep 24)
Tripped Out Cash: There's trouble in the shop as a woman catches her boyfriend secretly trying to flog her ring. Plus, Les lays his hands on some priceless rock memorabilia. (S7, ep 5)
Motor Mouth: Les is tempted to break one of the pawn shop's biggest rules, when a fast-talking client catches him off guard. (S7, ep 6)
Bohemian Pawnsody: When Rick gets a chance at an iconic collection of Hard Rock photographs, can he capture a deal or will another one bite the dust?

The Time Benders: As more people open their minds to UFOs and extraterrestrial visits from lightyears away, this episode explores whether aliens can bend both time and space. (S14, ep 10)

Hotspots: Some places are known for so many reports of UAP sightings that people flock from all around the world, just to catch a glimpse of a flying saucer. (S1, ep 8)
Falkirk Triangle: With more than 300 UFO sightings each year, the people living within the Falkirk Triangle can't help but feel uneasy about the strange occurrences. (S1, ep 6)
Shock and Awe: After the team's final experiment of the year, stunning revelations are made all across Skinwalker Ranch. (S5, ep 14)
